name: 21C hotel and museum / Counting House restaurant
directions: Multiple single bathrooms available on mezzanine floor and are open to anyone.
comment: Not advertised to public but no one will stop you. Each individual bathroom has unique signage and gender neutral logo and wording "We Don't Care" from artist Peregrine Honig with a portion of this quote: “I was reading trans and non-binary responses [to the bills] on social media and had the thought that there is something precious and intelligent about not caring. That eventually we will experience a generation of people who don’t care about where people go to the bathroom. I would like the sign to become standard until we simply remove gender from bathrooms completely. Large changes take small steps.” **Also the bathroom walls themselves are works of art where the walls are see through until you lock the door. Pretty cool!**

name: The Domain

comment: There are two entrances to the hallway. The one on the Paper Source side on Palm Way is usually locked. Go around to the Rock Rose side.

name: Mathias Hall

name: Nationwide

comment: only available to the public during working hours (I think 6-6 M-F)

name: 21C hotel and museum / Counting House restaurant
directions:
Restrooms are on mezzanine level of museum. There are a lot available, and each one is gender neutral, with signs on the inside indicating that "we don't care" and this quote: "“I was reading trans and non-binary responses [to the bills] on social media and had the thought that there is something precious and intelligent about not caring. That eventually we will experience a generation of people who don’t care about where people go to the bathroom. I would like the sign to become standard until we simply remove gender from bathrooms completely. Large changes take small steps.” - by artist Peregrine Honig
(Also the windows of each individual bathroom are clear until the user locks them - pretty cool!)
